# Privacy Policy for Krispr

\*\*Last updated: May 24, 2026

This Privacy Policy describes how Krispr ("we", "us", or "the app") collects, uses, and shares your information when you use our mobile application. By using Krispr, you agree to the practices described here.

> **Contact:** For any questions about this policy or your data, email **[krisprstudio@gmail.com]**.

## 1. Information We Collect

**Account information.** When you create an account, we collect your **email address**. You may optionally set a **username**. If you sign in with Google, we receive your email address and basic profile information from Google.

**Photos you submit.** When you enhance a photo, the image you select or capture is uploaded to our processing service so it can be enhanced by AI. See "How Your Photos Are Processed" below.

**Usage data.** We store a count of how many enhancements you have performed and the time of your most recent enhancement, in order to enforce free-tier limits and rate limits.

**Subscription information.** If you purchase a subscription, our payments provider (RevenueCat, via Apple) provides us with your subscription status and product identifier. We do **not** receive or store your full payment card details — those are handled by Apple.

We do **not** collect precise location, contacts, or device advertising identifiers, and we do **not** use third-party advertising.

## 2. How Your Photos Are Processed

When you request an enhancement:

1. Your photo is sent securely to our backend (Supabase Edge Function), which forwards it to **Google's Gemini AI image API** for enhancement and colorization.
2. The enhanced image is returned to your device and saved **locally on your device**. Enhanced images are not stored on our servers as part of normal operation.
3. Photos are transmitted to Google solely to perform the enhancement you requested. Your use of this feature is also subject to Google's privacy practices.

We do not use your photos to train models, and we do not sell your photos.

## 3. How We Use Your Information

- To provide and operate the app (authenticate you, process enhancements, save your history on your device).
- To enforce free-tier limits, cooldowns, and subscription entitlements.
- To respond to support requests.
- To maintain the security and integrity of the service.

## 4. Third-Party Services

We rely on the following service providers, each with its own privacy policy:

- **Supabase** — authentication, account data, and the secure function that proxies enhancement requests.
- **Google (Gemini API)** — AI image enhancement processing.
- **RevenueCat** — subscription management.
- **Apple** — App Store payments and in-app purchases.

We share only the information necessary for these providers to perform their function.

## 5. Data Retention

- **Account data** (email, username, usage counts, subscription status) is retained while your account exists.
- **Enhanced images** are stored on your device and are removed when you delete them in-app or uninstall the app.
- When you delete your account, your account record and associated data are deleted.

## 6. Your Rights & Account Deletion

You can **delete your account and associated data** at any time from within the app (Profile → Delete Account) or by emailing us at **[krisprstudio@gmail.com]**. Depending on your region, you may also have rights to access, correct, or export your personal data; contact us to exercise them.

## 7. Children's Privacy

Krispr is not directed to children under 13 (or the minimum age in your jurisdiction). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us information, contact us and we will delete it.

## 8. Security

We use industry-standard measures (encrypted transport, scoped access controls) to protect your information. No method of transmission or storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

## 9. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Material changes will be reflected by updating the "Last updated" date above and, where appropriate, by notice within the app.

